    <briefdescription>
<para>Application entry point — simulated patient monitoring session. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Demonstrates the Patient Vital Signs Monitor with two simulated patients:</para>
<para><bold>Patient 1 — Sarah Johnson (ID 1001)</bold> Simulates a deterioration trajectory across three readings:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Reading 1: All normal (admission baseline)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reading 2: All WARNING (developing sepsis-like presentation)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reading 3: Temperature and SpO2 CRITICAL (acute crisis)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><bold>Patient 2 — David Okonkwo (ID 1002)</bold> Simulates an isolated bradycardia episode:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Reading 1: All normal (stable)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reading 2: Heart rate CRITICAL (severe bradycardia at 38 bpm)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<sect1 id="main_8c_1autotoc_md1_1s1"><sect2 id="main_8c_1autotoc_md1_1s2"><sect3 id="main_8c_1autotoc_md1">
<title>Output Format</title><para>Each reading shows per-parameter classification in brackets and any active alerts prefixed with <computeroutput>! WARNING</computeroutput> or <computeroutput>!! CRITICAL</computeroutput>. A summary block is printed at the end of each patient&apos;s session.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="version"><para>1.0.0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="date"><para>2026-04-06 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="author"><para>vinu-engineer </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
